<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1066" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1066">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">833.61311/4–2446</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-24">April 24, 1946</date>.<lb/>[Received April
                                24—11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>255. By decree yesterday Government ordered expropriation of all stocks
                            of wheat and wheat flour and intervention of all establishments dealing
                            in OEE milling wheat. Intervention contemplates extensive <pb facs="1309" n="1291" xml:id="pg_1291"/> measures for regulating
                            milling use of flour and distribution of wheat and wheat products. For
                            present holders of wheat and flour are prohibited from supplying
                            customers more than 66% of 1945 average deliveries. Text by airmail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>